(
Figs. 1–3
)

Description. Parthenogenetic female.
General.
In lateral view, body yellow brownish, regularly ovoid, highly arched, maximum height at middle of body (body height/length ratio about 0.7 for adults) (
Figs. 1A
, 
2A
). In dorsal and anterior view body compressed laterally, dorsal keel absent (
Fig. 2B
). Dorsal margin uniformly curved, depression between head and rest of body absent (
Figs. 1A
, 
2A
). Posterodorsal and posteroventral angles expressed, obtuse (
Figs. 1A, F
; 
2A
). Posterior margin slightly convex or almost straight (
Figs. 1A, F
; 
2A
). Ventral margin almost straight; anteroventral angle rounded (
Figs. 1A, F
; 
2A
).

Head
small (
Figs. 1A, B
; 
2A, C
). Rostrum relatively short; compound eye larger than ocellus; distance from tip of rostrum to ocellus almost equal to distance between centers of ocellus and eye (
Figs. 1A, B
). Head shield with broadly rounded posterior portion (
Fig. 1C
). Head shield with three connected major head pores and two lateral slit-shaped pores (
Figs. 1C, D
; 
2E
). Major head pores subequal in size, middle pore located closer to posterior pore. Connection between anterior pore and middle pore narrow, clearly expressed (
Figs. 1C, D
; 
2E
). Connection between middle pore and posterior pore broad. PP less than 0.5 IP. Lateral pores slit-like with semicircular pockets, length of lateral pores about 0.6–0.8 IP, depth of pore pocket about half of pore length (
Figs. 1C, D
; 
2E
).

Labrum
large (
Fig. 1E
). Distal labral plate with tiny setulae. Labral keel with a regularly convex, not wavy anterior margin. Apex of keel rounded. Posterior margin of keel with two small rows of setulae (
Fig. 1E
).

Valve
large, ovoid (
Figs. 1A, F
; 
2A
). A row of numerous setulated setae on inner face of ventral and anteroventral margins of valve (
Figs. 1A, F, H, I
). Short setulae on inner face of posteroventral angle and posterior margin of valve (
Figs. 1A, F, G
; 
2G
). On outer face, valves with moderately developed sculpture, consisting of longitudinal, sometimes anastomosing lines, located in posterior and ventral portion of valves (
Figs. 1A, F
; 
2A, F
).

Postabdomen
moderately long, subrectangular, narrowing distally in postanal portion; length/height ratio about 2 (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H
). Ventral margin straight or slightly convex. Preanal and anal margin almost equal in length; postanal margin about 1.5 times longer than anal margin. Preanal and postanal angles well expressed. Basis of claws slightly inflated, bordered from distal margin by a clear incision (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H, J
). Postanal portion of postabdomen armed with robust composite marginal denticles, increasing in size distally (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H, J
). Proximally each denticle covered by short stiff spinules. Denticles in proximal portion of postanal margin significantly smaller and grouped in bunches (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H, I
). Postanal portion with row of 7–8 narrow clusters of thin short lateral setulae, distalmost setula in each cluster being longest; distance between postanal clusters 1.5 times greater than width of clusters. This row goes on anal margin, but setulae in the proximal clusters of this part have equal length (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H, I
).

Postabdominal claw
long (subequal in length than postanal margin of postabdomen), slightly curved (
Figs. 1J, K
; 
2H, J
). Its dorsal margin armed in outer side with a row of fine teeth, decreasing in size distally (
Figs. 1L
, 
2J
), and in inner side with a row of relatively robust teeth (
Fig. 2J
). Basal spine short, its length less that width of claw base (
Figs. 1L
, 
2J
). Basis of claw without a bunch of setulae (
Figs. 1L
, 
2J
).

Antenna I
relatively long, not reaching tip of rostrum, with four distinguishable rows of setulae (
Figs. 1A, B, M
; 
2K
). Antennular sensory seta slender, arising subdistally, shorter than antennular body (
Figs. 1M
, 
2K
). Nine aesthetascs, two of them longer than the rest, but shorter than antennular body. All aesthetascs tips projecting beyond tip of rostrum (
Figs. 1A, B
).

Limb III
(
Fig. 3D–F
) with ovoid epipodite. Exopodite (ext) almost round, with five distal setae (among which two middle setae short), and two lateral setae (
Figs. 3D, E
). Distal endite (in terms of 
Kotov (2013))
with three anterior setae (
Figs. 3D, F
): setae 1 and 2 supplied with short stiff setulae distally, a small sensillum between their bases, and seta 3 with fine long setulae. Proximal endite with four small anterior setae; a small sensillum near seta 4. Four soft setae on posterior face of limb (a–d). Distal armature of gnathobase with three setae and a thick sensillum. Filter plate with seven setae of subequal size.

Limb IV
(
Fig. 3G–J
) with ovoid bilobed densely setulated preepipodite. Epipodite (epp) ovoid, with long finger-like projection (
Figs. 3G, H
). Exopodite (ext) almost round, with three distal and three lateral setae. Inner distal portion with four anterior setae: distalmost seta 1 stout, naked; setae 2–4 shorter with inflated basal portion and relatively thick setulae distally (
Figs. 3G, I, J
). Three thin setae (a–c) on posterior limb face. Distal armature of gnathobase with two elements, one long bisegmented seta and a blunt process near it. Filter plate with five setae subequal in size (
Figs. 3G, I, J
).

Limb V
(
Fig. 3 K, L
) with ovoid bilobed densely setulated preepipodite (pep). Epipodite (epp) ovoid, with long finger-like projection. Exopodite (ext) bilobed, with four plumose setae: three long lateral setae separated from a single relatively short distal seta via densely setulated convex lobe (
Fig. 3K
). Inner limb portion as elongated flap, with setulated margin, with two setulated setae (1–2) of unequal length. Filter plate with three small setae of different length.
